Based on the code you shared, it seems that you are not clearing the previous state of the `bookedMK` array when a new data is fetched from Firebase. This can cause the previous data to be appended to the new data and result in duplicates.

To fix this, you can try clearing the `bookedMK` array when a new data is fetched using the `setBookedMK` function with an empty array. Here's an updated `useEffect` hook with this fix:

```
useEffect(() => {
   if (userId) {
     const userRef = firebase.database().ref(`users/${userId}`);
     userRef.on('value', snapshot => {
       const data = snapshot.val();
       setUserData(data);
     });

     const bookedMKRef = firebase.database().ref(`users/${userId}/bookedMK`);
     bookedMKRef.on('value', snapshot => {
